  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowerment and Accountability Research Program (Inception Phase)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Social and political action has been recognized as a pathway to empowerment and accountability in development for at least two decades. However, rapidly changing contexts, especially in fragile and conflict settings, challenge existing assumptions about how these goals can be achieved. New developments in digital technologies are changing the ways in which people can mobilize and act, governments can collect and use information about their citizens, and political groups, including radical movements like Islamic State, can seek popular support. Increased global interdependence and growing political and economic inequality further throw into question the validity of our existing knowledge. If we are to understand the pathways to empowerment and accountability in these new contexts, fresh conceptual, methodological and operational approaches are required.</narrative>
  </description>
